%3Cp%3EA%20Target%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20the%20company's%20foot%20traffic%20estimates%20don't%20account%20for%20the%20chain's%20recent%20growth%20in%20digital%20sales%2C%20including%20delivery%20and%20pick-up%20orders.%20Drive-up%20orders%20%E2%80%94%20brought%20directly%20to%20a%20customer's%20car%20so%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20set%20foot%20in%20the%20store%20%E2%80%94%20now%20make%20up%20almost%20half%20of%20Target's%20digital%20sales%2C%20CEO%20Cornell%20said%20on%20the%20company's%20earnings%20call%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20staffing%20levels%20appeared%20disproportionately%20high%20for%20the%20limited%20number%20of%20shoppers.%20Multiple%20employees%20were%20spotted%20on%20the%20floor%20during%20each%20visit%2C%20either%20refilling%20shelves%2C%20tending%20to%20displays%2C%20or%20engaged%20in%20casual%20conversation%20near%20the%20stock%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaunders%2C%20the%20analyst%2C%20said%20that%20even%20though%20plenty%20of%20employees%20might%20be%20out%20on%20the%20sales%20floor%2C%20they're%20often%20occupied%20with%20fulfilling%20e-commerce%20orders%20under%20tight%20deadlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20very%2C%20very%20thinly%20stretched%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22505aed7f-d350-4634-8c79-bae1393d2c2e%5C%22%3EA%20visit%20to%20a%20small-format%20Target%20store%20revealed%20some%20challenges%20facing%20the%20chain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Target%20store%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%20shows%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20the%20chain%20faces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20entrance%20to%20a%20Target%20store%20in%20Washington%20DC's%20Cleveland%20Park%20neighborhood%20on%20an%20overcast%20day%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b45c5f748d8c055f39d22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20small-format%20Target%20store%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Bitter%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20location%20is%20one%20of%20the%20small-format%20stores%20that%20Target%20started%20opening%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%20While%20typical%20suburban%20Targets%20are%20around%20125%2C000%20square%20feet%2C%20this%20store%20is%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bizjournals.com%2Fwashington%2Fnews%2F2017%2F11%2F02%2Ftarget-comes-to-cleveland-park-here-are-the-lease.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E23%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20smaller%20size%20has%20allowed%20Target%20to%20open%20stores%20in%20dense%20cities%20and%20other%20areas%20where%20opening%20a%20typical%20big-box%20isn't%20practical%2C%20Target%20executives%20have%20said.%20Cleveland%20Park%2C%20the%20DC%20neighborhood%20home%20to%20the%20store%20BI%20visited%2C%20is%20one%20such%20dense%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20recent%20visits%2C%20though%2C%20BI%20saw%20issues%20with%20shopping%20at%20the%20mini-Target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20wide%20range%20of%20items%2C%20from%20men's%20socks%20to%20deodorant%20to%20laundry%20detergent%2C%20were%20locked%20behind%20glass%20doors.%20Customers%20could%20press%20a%20call%20button%20for%20help%2C%20though%20when%20BI%20tried%20it%20during%20multiple%20visits%2C%20a%20Target%20employee%20only%20showed%20up%20about%20half%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Health%20and%20beauty%20products%2C%20including%20toothpaste%20and%20toothbrushes%2C%20are%20seen%20locked%20up%20in%20an%20aisle%20of%20a%20Target%20store.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b4616f748d8c055f39d2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EToothpaste%20is%20kept%20under%20lock%20and%20key%20at%20a%20Target%20store%3Cp%3EAlex%20Bitter%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20locked%20cases%20are%20likely%20an%20attempt%20to%20reduce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-stores-violent-retail-thefts-threats-violence-doubled-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etheft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20issue%20that%20Target%20and%20other%20retailers%20have%20struggled%20with%20in%20the%20past.%20Yet%20other%20stores%20in%20the%20area%2C%20including%20a%20Giant%20supermarket%2C%20a%20local%20health%20food%20store%2C%20and%20a%20CVS%2C%20offered%20many%20of%20the%20same%20products%20without%20having%20to%20get%20an%20employee%20to%20unlock%20a%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20times%2C%20staffing%20also%20appeared%20to%20be%20an%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20DC%20Target%20had%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbooths-grocery-chain-removed-self-service-checkouts-staff-prefer-it-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eself-checkout%3C%2Fa%3E%20kiosks%20and%20person-powered%20checkouts%2C%20there%20were%20times%20when%20BI%20visited%20when%20no%20one%20was%20immediately%20at%20the%20register%20to%20ring%20customers%20up%20or%20assist%20with%20a%20pick-up%20order.%20During%20one%20visit%2C%20BI%20saw%20a%20customer%20wandering%20around%20as%20she%20looked%20for%20an%20employee%20who%20could%20help%20her%20buy%20a%20gift%20card%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20Target's%20self-checkout%20stations%20can't%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Target%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20the%20retailer%20has%20spent%20the%20last%20year%20adding%20more%20checkout%20stations%20staffed%20by%20people.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20company%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.target.com%2Fnews-features%2Farticle%2F2025%2F05%2Fself-checkout%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadded%3C%2Fa%3E%20Express%20self-checkout%20lanes%20for%20customers%20with%2010%20items%20or%20fewer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20BI%20visited%20this%20store%2C%20most%20products%20were%20in%20stock.%20A%20few%20areas%2C%20such%20as%20a%20locked%20case%20for%20Apple%20accessories%20and%20the%20kitchen%20appliance%20department%2C%20had%20bare%20shelves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mostly%20empty%20locked%20case%20meant%20to%20carry%20Apple%20accessories%20such%20as%20earbuds%20and%20charging%20cables%20at%20a%20Target%20store.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b466af748d8c055f39d39%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20locked%20case%20meant%20for%20Apple%20accessories%20was%20mostly%20empty%20when%20BI%20visited%20this%20Target%20store.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Bitter%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20normal%20Target%20would%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20wider%20array%20of%20alternative%20products%20for%20shoppers%20in%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20in%20a%20small%20store%20with%20a%20narrow%20product%20selection%2C%20out-of-stocks%20increase%20the%20chance%20that%20shoppers%20will%20leave%20without%20buying%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221a6215aa-9199-4807-b5d8-45ee0798809b%5C%22%3EIt's%20a%20mixed%20bag%20for%20Target%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20visits%20suggest%20that%20Target%20is%20not%20in%20any%20sort%20of%20crisis%20like%20the%20ones%20that%20have%20wiped%20out%20many%20other%20retail%20brands%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20stores%20we%20visited%20were%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eclean%2C%20the%20merchandise%20was%20usually%20presentable%2C%20the%20staff%20were%20mostly%20available%2C%20and%20the%20shopping%20experience%20was%20generally%20pleasant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20assortment%20is%20not%20especially%20exciting%2C%20and%20the%20prices%20aren't%20meaningfully%20better%20than%20those%20at%20a%20competitor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Bullseye's%20Playground%20section%20of%20a%20Target%20in%20Wisconsin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b438d85e81483682c037b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Bullseye's%20Playground%20section%20of%20a%20Target%20in%20Wisconsin.%3Cp%3EDominick%20Reuter%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20might%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20win%20over%20shoppers%20in%202025%2C%20who%20are%20increasingly%20picky%20about%20finding%20good%20deals%20or%20at%20least%20a%20reason%20to%20splurge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20issues%20with%20Target%20is%20it%20really%20has%20lost%20its%20focus%2C%20as%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20retailers%20have%20increased%20and%20improved%20their%20focus%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%20recently%20created%20an%20Enterprise%20Acceleration%20Office%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeliver%20faster%20progress%26quot%3B%20on%20its%20growth%20plans%2C%20said%20a%20May%20announcement%20that%20Target's%20spokesperson%20referred%20BI%20to.%20The%20effort%20will%20include%20using%20technology%20to%20better%20manage%20Target's%20inventory%2C%20for%20example%2C%20CFO%20Michael%20Fiddelke%20said%20on%20last%20month's%20earnings%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20major%20retailers%20are%20investing%20heavily%20in%20delivering%20the%20most%20convenience%20(think%3A%20Walmart)%2C%20the%20best%20prices%20(Costco)%2C%20the%20biggest%20surprises%20(T.J.%20Maxx)%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20those%20things%20(Amazon).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20are%20areas%20Target%20continues%20to%20struggle%20in%20as%20it%20looks%20to%20grow%20its%20revenue%20and%20store%20visits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20an%20existential%20crisis%20for%20Target%2C%26quot%3B%20Saunders%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they%20need%20to%20get%20out%20of%20this%20nosedive%20and%20at%20least%20get%20the%20plane%20on%20a%20level%20heading.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-store-visits-why-company-struggling-images