its.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELetizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%20built%20a%20portfolio%20of%20cash-flowing%20rental%20properties%20to%20buy%20back%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20physician%20couple%20had%20spent%20their%20early%20careers%20working%20up%20to%2080-hour%20workweeks%20in%20the%20hospital%20and%20wanted%20their%20future%20lifestyle%20to%20look%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20shortly%20after%20getting%20married%2C%20they%20set%20a%20specific%20cash%20flow%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20said%2C%20'We're%20going%20to%20replace%20both%20our%20clinical%20incomes%20in%20seven%20years%2C'%26quot%3B%20Alto%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we%20were%20always%20working%20toward%3A%20To%20get%20to%20the%20space%20where%20we%20had%20time%20freedom.%20We%20wanted%20time%20with%20each%20other%20and%20we%20wanted%20time%20with%20our%20kids%20growing%20up%2C%20so%20we%20didn't%20miss%20everything%20that%20we%20saw%20all%20the%20doctors%20around%20us%20missing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20immediately%20got%20to%20work%2C%20redirecting%20the%20money%20they'd%20saved%20to%20buy%20their%20first%20primary%20home%20into%20their%20first%20two%20investment%20properties.%20As%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-profitable-rental-business-retire-early-financial-freedom-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexpanded%20to%20over%20100%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20remained%20tenants%20themselves%20up%20until%202022%2C%20when%20they%20moved%20to%20Puerto%20Rico%20and%20bought%20a%20home.%20The%20couple%20has%20scaled%20back%20on%20medicine%20and%20spends%20most%20of%20their%20time%20managing%20their%20portfolio%2C%20building%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsemiretiredmd.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESemi-Retired%20MD%3C%2Fa%3E%20community%2C%20and%20traveling%20with%20their%20three%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20big%20differentiator%20is%20that%20we%20apply%20a%20lot%20of%20business%20principles%20to%20our%20rental%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Asakura.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20think%20about%20rental%20properties%20as%20a%20business%20%E2%80%94%20they%20think%20about%20it%20as%20providing%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20but%20ultimately%2C%20each%20property%20is%20a%20mini-business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20six%20main%20ways%20to%20make%20money%20in%20the%20business%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20added%20Alto%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20our%20goal%20is%20to%20tap%20into%20all%20of%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2218adbc98-41c1-4364-93a0-a267d12666ac%5C%22%3E1.%20Cash%20flow%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20buy%20and%20rent%20an%20investment%20property%2C%20you%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20generate%20cash%20flow%2C%20which%20is%20your%20rental%20income%20minus%20all%20of%20your%20expenses.%20Positive%20cash%20flow%20is%20a%20focus%20and%20a%20requirement%20for%20Alto%20and%20Asakura.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20feel%20confident%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20select%20strong%20cash-flowing%20properties%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20cash-on-cash%20calculator%20they%20created%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20input%20metrics%20such%20as%20purchase%20price%2C%20expenses%2C%20and%20projected%20rents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20purchasing%20anything%2C%20they%20run%20the%20numbers%20twice%20%E2%80%94%20first%20to%20see%20if%20it's%20even%20worth%20submitting%20an%20offer.%20Then%2C%20once%20they%20have%20a%20property%20under%20contract%2C%20they'll%20do%20a%20run-through%20with%20their%20inspector%2C%20property%20manager%2C%20real%20estate%20agent%2C%20contractor%2C%20and%20insurance%20broker.%20Each%20team%20member%20can%20weigh%20in%20on%20various%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20contractor%2C%20for%20example%2C%20can%20confirm%20whether%20their%20renovation%20cost%20estimate%20is%20accurate%2C%20while%20their%20property%20manager%20can%20confirm%20the%20amount%20of%20rent%20the%20property%20will%20likely%20generate.%20Then%2C%20they'll%20enter%20the%20new%2C%20more%20accurate%20numbers%20into%20their%20calculator%20and%20have%20more%20certainty%20around%20how%20the%20property%20will%20perform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20say%20we%20thought%20it%20was%20going%20to%20perform%20a%20certain%20way%2C%20we%20did%20our%20due%20diligence%2C%20and%20there%20were%20all%20these%20problems%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20repair%2C%20and%20the%20cash-on-cash%20is%20now%20not%20worth%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20we%20negotiate%20and%20try%20to%20get%20the%20price%20down.%20Or%2C%20we%20try%20to%20get%20credits%20to%20get%20it%20to%20where%20the%20deal%20still%20works%20for%20the%20cash-on-cash%20return.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20deal%20doesn't%20work%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20don't%20buy%20the%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20not%20buy%20something%20that's%20going%20to%20be%20cash%20flow%20negative%20or%20cash%20flow%20neutral.%20We%20really%20want%20a%20cash-on-cash%20return%20because%20that's%20ultimately%20the%20income%20that%20sets%20us%20free.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2221779263-c49b-4c9a-8d02-d3ea3813dee0%5C%22%3E2.%20Debt%20pay%20down%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmortgage-buy-down-interest-rate-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMortgage%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%20build%20equity%2C%20so%20every%20time%20you%20make%20a%20payment%2C%20you%20build%20a%20bigger%20stake%20in%20the%20property%20until%20you%20own%20the%20asset%20outright.%20The%20great%20thing%20about%20having%20tenants%20is%20that%20their%20rent%20is%20helping%20you%20build%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20cash%20flowing%2C%20your%20tenants%20are%20paying%20down%20your%20mortgage%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kenji%20leti%20semi-retired%20MD%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c4beb3d5881a51c1b62f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlto%20and%20Asakura%20started%20buying%20investment%20properties%20in%202015.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c2683a9-b17f-4dcc-9c96-c56e687afc20%5C%22%3E3.%20Forced%20appreciation%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EForced%20appreciation%20is%20when%20the%20investor%20increases%20the%20value%20of%20the%20property.%20To%20do%20so%2C%20Alto%20and%20Asakura%20focus%20on%20increasing%20the%20net%20operating%20income%20(NOI)%20by%20increasing%20income%20or%20decreasing%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasing%20income%20can%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20increasing%20rent%20if%20it's%20below%20market%20value.%20Or%2C%20with%20a%20bit%20of%20creativity%2C%20you%20could%20rent%20unused%20spaces%20of%20your%20land%20or%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20increase%20revenue%20of%20your%20property%20even%20more%20by%20tapping%20into%20what%20we%20call%20hidden%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Asakura.%20%26quot%3BThat%20might%20mean%20renting%20out%20a%20storage%20unit%2C%20turning%20a%20garage%20into%20a%20workspace%2C%20or%20adding%20a%20bedroom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20decreasing%20expenses%2C%20one%20strategy%20they've%20used%20is%20charging%20back%20utilities.%20For%20example%2C%20on%20a%20property%20with%20a%20detached%20garage%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20set%20it%20up%20so%20it%20could%20be%20used%20as%20a%20workshop.%20They%20ran%20separate%20electricity%20to%20the%20garage%2C%20rented%20the%20space%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20hundred%20dollars%20a%20month%2C%20and%20billed%20back%20the%20utilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20increase%20income%20and%20decrease%20expenses%2C%20the%20property%20creates%20more%20cash%20flow%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20it's%20worth%20more%20to%20the%20next%20investor%20because%20the%20next%20investor%20is%20buying%20it%20to%20make%20cash%20flow%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto%2C%20adding%20that%20forcing%20appreciation%20has%20made%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20difference%20for%20the%20growth%20of%20our%20net%20worth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226cb5076d-7961-4d7f-8c8e-0554cfc37142%5C%22%3E4.%20Immediate%20appreciation%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EImmediate%20appreciation%20is%20just%20as%20it%20sounds%3A%20%26quot%3BDay%201%2C%20you%20make%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20it%20appraised%20and%20it's%20worth%20more%20than%20what%20you%20purchased%20it%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20capitalize%20on%20this%20type%20of%20appreciation%20by%20recognizing%20good%20deals%20and%20acting%20quickly%2C%20negotiating%20with%20the%20seller%2C%20and%20leveraging%20your%20network%20to%20find%20off-market%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bbab9fee-17fe-45ad-baeb-c4dec3b5ee0f%5C%22%3E5.%20Market%20appreciation%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20control%20market%20appreciation.%20That's%20a%20lesson%20Asakura%20learned%20from%20investing%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20He%20was%20essentially%20buying%20land%2C%20waiting%20for%20it%20to%20increase%20in%20value%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20during%20that%20era%2C%20most%20real%20estate%20was%20%E2%80%94%20and%20selling%20it%20for%20profit.%20That%20worked%20until%20the%202008%20housing%20market%20crash%2C%20which%20left%20him%20exposed%20and%20%26quot%3Bstuck%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20mortgages%2C%20insurance%20payments%2C%20and%20property%20taxes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20lesson%20was%20to%20never%20depend%20on%20market%20appreciation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20set%20yourself%20up%20to%20make%20it%20more%20likely%20to%20happen%20by%20buying%20in%20the%20path%20of%20progress%20of%20a%20particular%20neighborhood%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20have%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20likelihood%20of%20market%20appreciation%2C%20but%20again%2C%20you%20cannot%20control%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Letizia%20alto%20kenji%20asakura%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684b29fe85e81483682bff0e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlto%20and%20Asakura%20reside%20in%20Puerto%20Rico%20but%20travel%20about%20six%20months%20a%20year.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Letizia%20Alto%20and%20Kenji%20Asakura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220dbd435-ae2b-4776-aaeb-5402db062155%5C%22%3E6.%20Tax%20benefits%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20to%20the%20couple's%20strategy%20is%20tapping%20into%20tax%20benefits%20specifically%20for%20real%20estate%20investors.%20Especially%20when%20they%20first%20started%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20they%20used%20big%20tax%20refunds%20to%20buy%20more%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tax%20code%20is%20essentially%20a%20series%20of%20incentives%20to%20encourage%20certain%20behavior%20that%20the%20government%20wants%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Asakura.%20The%20trick%20is%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20use%20it%20to%20your%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftax-saving-strategies-for-real-estate-investors-property-owners-landlords-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20use%20is%20sheltering%20their%20income%20using%20a%20status%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Breal%20estate%20professional%20status%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20REPS.%20To%20qualify%2C%20real%20estate%20has%20to%20be%20your%20primary%20job.%20There%20are%20stipulations%20set%20by%20the%20IRS%2C%20including%20spending%20more%20than%20750%20hours%20on%20real-estate%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20meet%20the%20criteria%2C%20your%20passive%20losses%20from%20rental%20real%20estate%20are%20considered%20non-passive%2C%20and%20you%20can%20offset%20your%20W2%20or%201099%20income%2C%20which%20could%20lower%20your%20taxable%20income%20significantly%20and%20place%20you%20in%20a%20lower%20tax%20bracket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsakura%20transitioned%20to%20a%20part-time%20hospitalist%20in%202015%20so%20he%20could%20qualify%20for%20the%20status.%20Only%20one%20spouse%20needs%20to%20qualify%2C%20meaning%20Alto%20could%20continue%20working%20and%20deduct%20the%20real%20estate%20losses%20from%20her%20clinical%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20the%20first%20year%20Asakura%20qualified%20for%20REPS%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20did%20a%20lot%20of%20rehabbing%20to%20create%20our%20losses%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Alto.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20rehabbed%2C%20we%20would%20be%20increasing%20the%20value%20of%20the%20property%20and%20increasing%20cash%20flow%20of%20the%20property%2C%20but%20the%20rehab%20was%20a%20write-off%2C%20which%20was%20insane.%20I%20hope%20people%20understand%20that%20rehabbing%20is%20such%20an%20incredible%20thing%20to%20do%20because%20it%20is%20tax%20beneficial%2C%20but%20you%20get%20to%20keep%20all%20the%20upside%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-from-real-estate-cashflow-financial-independence-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750064702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684c561885e81483682c12bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-money-from-real-estate-cashflow-financial-independence-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20think%20about%20rental%20properties%20as%20a%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20investor%20Kenji%20Asakura.%20%26quot%3BBut%20ultimately%2C%20each%20property%20is%20a%20mini-business.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%