ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fblog%2Fclass-of-2025-young-workers-were-poised-to-graduate-into-a-promising-labor-market-but-trump-policy-actions-could-unravel-progress%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20labor%20market%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20May%20indicates%20that%20even%20after%20adjusting%20for%20inflation%2C%2016-%20to%2024-year-old%20workers%20experienced%20historically%20strong%20wage%20growth%20of%209.1%25%20from%20February%202020%20to%20March%20of%20this%20year%2C%20a%20figure%20that%20exceeded%20wage%20growth%20for%20workers%2025%20and%20older%20(5.4%25).%20The%20cohort%20was%20set%20to%20have%20lower%20average%20unemployment%20rates%20and%20better%20job%20opportunities%20than%20every%20other%20set%20of%20young%20workers%20since%20the%201990s.%20But%20the%20rosy%20picture%20has%20rapidly%20worsened.%20Job%20prospects%20for%2022-%20to%2027-year-olds%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20higher%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorkfed.org%2Fresearch%2Fcollege-labor-market%23--%3Aoverview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeteriorated%20noticeably%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20this%20year%2C%20per%20the%20New%20York%20Fed%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Feconomy%2Farchive%2F2025%2F04%2Fjob-market-youth%2F682641%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent-grad%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20overall%20unemployment%20rate%20and%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20for%20people%20who%20recently%20graduated%20from%20college%20%E2%80%94%20just%20hit%20its%20widest%20point%20in%20at%20least%2040%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worth%20noting%20that%20previous%20generations%20have%20faced%20tough%20labor%20markets%3A%20Some%20baby%20boomers%20launched%20their%20careers%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%201970s%20stagflation%2C%20and%20millennials%20were%20looking%20for%20jobs%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis.%20But%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20seeing%20the%20start%20of%20a%20troubling%20trend.%20Educated%20Zoomers%2C%20specifically%2C%20are%20now%20more%20unemployed%20than%20the%20rest%20of%20America%2C%20something%20that%20didn't%20happen%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%20or%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20dot-com%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20overall%20unemployment%20rate%20goes%20up%20a%20little%20bit%20more%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20people%20always%20understand%20that%20that%20is%20what%20happens%3A%20the%20'last%20hired%2C%20first%20fired'%20phenomenon%2C%26quot%3B%20Gould%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20going%20to%20do%20at%20that%20point%3F%20You've%20gone%20into%20debt%20going%20to%20school%2C%20you've%20already%20decided%20your%20major%2C%20you've%20already%20made%20all%20those%20investments.%20It's%20very%20hard%20to%20shift.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FRNo8M%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22443%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economists%20I%20spoke%20with%20emphasized%20that%20there%20were%20solutions%20to%20the%20Gen%20Z%20career%20cliff%2C%20but%20things%20may%20get%20worse%20before%20they%20get%20better.%20Mansfield%20said%20some%20sectors%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-healthcare-education-restaurants-leisure-hospitality-hiring-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20caregiving%20and%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20could%20see%20increased%20labor%20demand%20as%20baby%20boomers%20and%20Gen%20Xers%20grow%20older%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20those%20opportunities%20aren't%20as%20attractive%20to%20people%20trained%20to%20do%20something%20else%2C%20like%20law%20or%20finance.%20He%20added%20that%20as%20AI%20becomes%20more%20integrated%20into%20the%20economy%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20later%20generations%20will%20most%20likely%20start%20to%20find%20roles%20in%20careers%20that%20don't%20exist%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKline%2C%20the%20recent%20Florida%20State%20grad%2C%20is%20banking%20on%20some%20sort%20of%20turnaround.%20Even%20as%20opportunities%20for%20people%20with%20advanced%20degrees%20dry%20up%2C%20she%20thinks%20the%20master's%20and%20some%20more%20internships%20will%20make%20her%20resum%C3%A9%20that%20much%20more%20attractive%20to%20prospective%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20reminding%20myself%20that%20it%20will%20be%20worth%20it%2C%20taking%20all%20these%20loans%20will%20be%20worth%20it%2C%20because%20having%20this%20master's%20degree%20will%20get%20me%20further%20and%20give%20me%20a%20better%20chance%20at%20a%20job%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20Kline%20said%2C%20adding.%20%26quot%3BBefore%20I%20came%20back%20to%20school%2C%20that%20was%20one%20of%20the%20loneliest%20times%20of%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarket%20conditions%20are%20changing%20how%20ambitious%20Gen%20Zers%20see%20themselves%20and%20their%20work.%20It%20isn't%20just%20about%20whether%20they%20can%20land%20a%20job%20after%20graduation.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20my%20age%20feel%20that%20open%20doors%20older%20generations%20took%20for%20granted%20%E2%80%94%20having%20access%20to%20homeownership%20and%20retirement%2C%20affording%20kids%20or%20healthcare%20or%20further%20education%20%E2%80%94%20are%20being%20locked%20alongside%20our%20career%20paths.%20It's%20part%20of%20why%20young%20people%20are%20becoming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-job-satisfaction-unhappy-work-salary-promotion-loyalty-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20loyal%20to%20the%20grind%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20giving%20up%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblue-collar-job-demand-growth-white-collar-layoffs-ai-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditionally%20white%20collar%20careers%3C%2Fa%3E%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20why%20Isabella%20Clemmens%2C%2022%2C%20is%20betting%20on%20herself.%20After%20graduating%20from%20Oregon%20State%20in%20May%2C%20she's%20moving%20to%20Austin%20to%20try%20out%20a%20new%20city%2C%20meet%20friends%2C%20attend%20concerts%2C%20and%20try%20living%20on%20her%20own.%20When%20Clemmens%20and%20I%20spoke%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20she%20was%20planning%20to%20work%20in%20retail%20until%20her%20growing%20stack%20of%20applications%20landed%20her%20a%20branding%20or%20graphic%20design%20role.%20After%20four%20years%20of%20hard%20work%2C%20she%20hadn't%20expected%20her%20job%20hunt%20to%20be%20so%20challenging.%20To%20kick%20off%20postgrad%20life%20in%20Texas%2C%20though%2C%20she%20would%20have%20to%20make%20concessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20dream%20job%20might%20exist%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I'm%20one%20of%20400%20people%20applying%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fallie-kelly%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAllie%20Kelly%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Economy%20team.%20She%20writes%20about%20social%20safety%20nets%20and%20how%20policy%20affects%20people.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750060981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684ae5cc85e81483682bf624%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20entry-level%20jobs%20disappear%20